				\begin{document}$$r_i$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M32"><mml:msub><mml:mi>r</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="122_2019_3424_Article_IEq16.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the radius of circle <italic>i</italic>. The factor <italic>k</italic> is 1.15. The planting density was then calculated as the inverse of the growing area.</p>
      </sec>
    </sec>
    <sec id="Sec7">
      <title>Statistical models</title>
      <p id="Par25">We assumed to have <italic>n</italic> plots such that a single field trial was indexed by the rows and columns of an <inline-formula id="IEq17"><alternatives><tex-math id="M33">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
