				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\mathrm{AR1} \otimes \mathrm{AR1}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M400"><mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">AR</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mo>⊗</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">AR</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="122_2019_3424_Article_IEq186.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and Matérn models managed to capture the spatial pattern in the observations, whereas the NoSpatial model and <inline-formula id="IEq187"><alternatives><tex-math id="M401">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
